Sentencas: The samples of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+delta (x=0.8, 1.0, 1.2) as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) were synthesized by solid-state reaction.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties were investigated by XRD, SEM, dilatometry, DC four-probe method, AC impedance and cyclic voltammetry (CV) techniques, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The XRD results showed all the samples obtained as a single K2NiF4-structural phase, there were no chemical reaction occurred between the Pr0.8Sr1.2CoO4+delta electrode and the Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte at 1100 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficients (TECs) increased with Sr content increasing.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the specimens was over 100S/cm at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The polarization resistance decreased with the increasing of Sr content.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Pr0.8Sr1.2O4+delta had the optimum value of 0.29 Omega center dot cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of Pr2-xSrxCoO4+δ Cathode Materials for IT-SOFC
